    "eyebrow": "Shaping",
    "num": "07",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Shaping</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Preparing Dough for Baking</h2><ul><li>Shape dough into desired form (loaf, boule, etc.).</li><li>Removes large gas bubbles for even crumb.</li><li>Prepares dough for final proofing and oven spring.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Shaping organizes the dough structure, ensuring even texture and good rise during baking. It also influences the bread’s final appearance [s1]. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s1\">[1]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Forming dough into a tight loaf shape before placing in a pan.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain why shaping is important before baking.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Poor shaping can cause uneven crumb or collapse during baking.</p></div></div>",
