    "eyebrow": "Summary",
    "num": "13",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">13</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Summary</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Key Takeaways on Bread Baking</h2><ul><li>Bread baking involves mixing, kneading, fermenting, shaping, and baking.</li><li>Flour, water, yeast, and salt are essential ingredients with specific roles.</li><li>Common problems often relate to process errors.</li><li>Current knowledge is provisional; experimentation and documentation are vital.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This overview summarizes the basic bread baking process and ingredient roles, highlights common challenges, and stresses the provisional nature of current knowledge [s1]. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s1\">[1]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A simple loaf made by following these steps and adjusting based on observations.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Review your understanding of bread baking steps and ingredient functions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking the importance of process control and evidence limitations.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide13\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:1,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;What should factual claims in bake bread connect back to?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;The approved source paper&quot;,&quot;A guess from the topic&quot;,&quot;A random online post&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;Every factual claim should connect to the approved source paper or be removed.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;tf&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Terminal and enabling learning objectives should be finalized after knowledge-base analysis.&quot;,&quot;answer&quot;:true,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The objectives need to match the sources, learner profile, and scope rules.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Name one thing the source-verification gate should block.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Mentions unsupported claims, fabricated sources, unresolved citations, or out-of-scope material.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;It should block unsupported claims that do not connect to the approved source paper.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;unsupported&quot;,&quot;fabricated&quot;,&quot;citation&quot;,&quot;out of scope&quot;,&quot;source&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>"
