    "id": "slide14",
    "eyebrow": "Practice",
    "num": "14",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">14</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Plan Your First Bread Bake</h2><ul><li>Choose a simple recipe with basic ingredients.</li><li>Prepare ingredients and workspace.</li><li>Follow mixing, kneading, fermenting, shaping, and baking steps.</li><li>Observe and note dough behavior and final bread quality.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Applying knowledge through practice helps solidify understanding and reveals areas needing adjustment [s1]. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s1\">[1]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Mixing 3 cups flour, 1 cup water, 1 tsp yeast, 1 tsp salt; kneading 10 minutes; fermenting 1 hour; shaping; baking 30 minutes at 375°F.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write your plan for your first bread bake including timing and observations to track.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Rushing steps or skipping notes reduces learning opportunities.</p></div></div>",
