    "id": "slide15",
    "eyebrow": "Reflection",
    "num": "15",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">15</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Reflection</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Evaluating Your Bread Baking Results</h2><ul><li>Assess bread texture, rise, crust, and flavor.</li><li>Compare outcomes to your planned expectations.</li><li>Identify what worked and what needs improvement.</li><li>Plan adjustments for next bake.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Reflecting on results helps refine technique and deepen understanding despite limited formal evidence [s1]. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s1\">[1]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Noticing dense crumb and deciding to knead longer next time.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief evaluation of your bread bake and list possible improvements.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring failures or not linking outcomes to process steps.</p></div></div>"
