    "eyebrow": "Transfer",
    "num": "16",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">16</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Transfer</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Applying Bread Baking Skills Elsewhere</h2><ul><li>Use ingredient knowledge in other baking recipes.</li><li>Adapt fermentation principles to other yeast-leavened foods.</li><li>Apply troubleshooting and observation skills broadly.</li><li>Recognize evidence limitations in other cooking areas.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Skills and critical thinking developed in bread baking transfer to wider culinary contexts, enhancing overall cooking competence [s1]. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s1\">[1]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Using yeast fermentation knowledge to make pizza dough.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify other recipes or cooking tasks where bread baking skills apply.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming all cooking processes have the same evidence base or troubleshooting methods.</p></div></div>",
    "words": "key-takeaway"
