    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">24</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Plan Your Bread Baking Experiment</h2><ul><li>Choose a recipe and set variables to test.</li><li>Decide what to observe and record.</li><li>Prepare to adjust one factor at a time.</li><li>Document your process and results.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Planning experiments supports evidence-based learning and skill development [s1]. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s1\">[1]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Testing different kneading times while keeping other factors constant.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write your experiment plan including variables and observations.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Changing multiple variables simultaneously.</p></div></div><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Presenter expansion:</strong> Ask learners to restate the point, apply it to one realistic situation, and identify the evidence they would need before acting independently.</p><p><strong>Bernard prompt:</strong> If the learner is unsure, have Bernard rephrase this slide in plain language while staying inside the cited source boundary.</p></div>",
