    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">25</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Reflect on Your Baking Experiment</h2><ul><li>Review your notes and outcomes.</li><li>Identify what changes improved or worsened bread.</li><li>Plan next steps based on reflection.</li><li>Share findings with peers or mentors.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Reflection consolidates learning and guides future improvements [s1]. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s1\">[1]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Noting that longer fermentation improved rise but affected flavor.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a reflection summarizing your experiment results.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Failing to link outcomes to specific process changes.</p></div></div><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Presenter expansion:</strong> Ask learners to restate the point, apply it to one realistic situation, and identify the evidence they would need before acting independently.</p><p><strong>Bernard prompt:</strong> If the learner is unsure, have Bernard rephrase this slide in plain language while staying inside the cited source boundary.</p></div>"
